<p class="text">
	After login each user gets his department's dashboard page (there are 15 departments at all)
	with a list of available actions, saved queries and notifications.
</p>

<div class="image_std">
	<img src="images/2_kgs/2_table.png">
	<span>Table of useful data</span>
</div>

<p class="text">
	In the general case any register or list of processes is just a table.
	There are two big problems with these tables: a large vertical size (tens of thousands of objects)
	and a large horizontal size (large number of columns, which often does not fit in 1024px wide).
	Therefore, information was placed in these tables very densely.
</p>
<div class="image_std">
	<img src="images/2_kgs/3_bigtable.png">
	<span>Table with periodic filters and relative changes</span>
</div>

<p class="text">
	Also there is a set of custom tables, which need to meet specific users' requirements.
	For example, a periodic table with relative data changes.
</p>
<div class="image_std">
	<img src="images/2_kgs/4_element.png">
	<span>Record edit page</span>
</div>

<p class="text">
	Generally, edit page of the object or process is a card with a set of fields with minimum possible number
	of field types. In the right part of the page is fixed block with navigation to quickly select every
	part of record card. This block can be turned off If it is necessary.
</p>


